						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone set up at the front gateway of the temple of Paramēs11vara.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1127-28.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged inscription dated in <hi rend="bold">Chālukya-Vikrama year 5[2], Plavaṅga, Sunday</hi> seems to refer to the death of some person, probably in a fight at <hi rend="bold">Kannavaḷḷi.</hi> The year cited corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1127-28.</hi></p>						

